data.enText: going to happen, be published, etc. very soon

data.chText: 近期将出版书籍的目录
乐队即将在英国的巡回演出

data.enText: ready or made available when needed
willing to give information about sth

data.chText: 她一直不很愿意说出自己的计划。
data.enText: She's never very forthcoming about her plans.

tr: available when required or as promised
at ease in talking to others

value.def: A forthcoming event is planned to happen soon.

example.tran: 他在即将来临的选举中的对手们

value.tran: 即将来临的;即将发生的

value.def: If something that you want, need, or expect is forthcoming, it is given to you or it happens.

example.ex: They promised that the money would be forthcoming...
We must first see some real evidence. So far it has not been forthcoming...
example.tran: 我们必须先看到一些实证，而到目前为止并没有看到。

example.ex: One source predicts no major shift in policy will be forthcoming at the committee hearings.
example.tran: 一位消息人士预测委员会听证会不会在政策上作出重大转变。

value.tran: 会发生的;现成的;可得到的

value.def: If you say that someone is forthcoming, you mean that they willingly give information when you ask them.
value.tran: 乐于提供信息的;愿意提供帮助的
